$ VIM: runtime

? The variable `$VIMRUNTIME` should point to the root of the runtime files.

→ development/vim/sources/runtime/optwin_vim

sa:
  → development/vim/sources/src/scriptfile_c contains functions for dealing with the runtime directories/files.

  → development/vim/sources/src/misc1_c#vim-src-misc1-vim_version_dir[`vim_version_dir()` in `misc1.c`]

  The directory name of the runtime files is assigned to the macro `RUNTIME_DIRNAME` (→ development/vim/sources/src/feature_h) (typically `runtime`).
